Rosemary is a sweet, 5 year old, Catahoula Hound mix. She enjoys walks, playing with toys, hanging out with her dog friends, and cuddling with her favorite people. Rosemary was found as stray, so there is no information about her past. Rosemary is proof that dogs are resilient and regardless of her circumstances she loves and trusts with all her soul. Currently Rosemary is being treated for heartworms and is apart of our 'Foster to Adopt' program. If you are interested in adopting Rosemary please bring the family and any other dogs in to meet her!

You can find all of our adoptable animals, as well as our Adoption Center hours, on our website: FriendsofStrays.org

Update on our newest friend, Brent:

After being rescued from death row at the ACC, Brent is now relaxing and gaining his strength at our shelter. He was severely dehydrated, underweight, and showing symptoms of a severe upper respiratory infection. These are all problems that are easily treatable, but at a crowded Brooklyn shelter, it was enough to land him on the euthanasia list.
We're thankful for the support we receive that makes it possible for us to rescue animals in need, like Brent. **STAY TUNED** We were able to rescue another furry friend - a senior dog - from death row at the ACC! We'll let you know when she gets here!

To sponsor Brent: https://southamptonanimalshelter.com/sponsor-a-pet/

To make a general donation: https://southamptonanimalshelter.com/dedication-donation/

PayPal: adrienne@sasfinc.org #adoptdontshop #adoptlove #cat #catsofinstagram #rescuecat

AVAILABLE FOR ADOPTION!!! Eli is a handsome, terrier mix puppy born around 12/2/2017 who had a very rough start in life. He and his sister were found on the side of a road in a box. A good samaritan found them and brought them to a local shelter. Even though Eli could be a shy, frightened puppy, he can't help but love everyone and his tail never stops wagging! He is just a super happy little guy. He loves to play with is sister, but loves to play with all of his foster brothers and sisters as well. He will need a structural fenced in back yard to run and play. Due to his age, he will need someone who is home more often than not and children who are ages 5 and up. Eli will make a wonderful family dog, or a great companion to someone who is looking for a buddy! His most favorite thing is to be held and loved. He just can't get enough affection. He currently weighs 8 pounds and may weigh around 45 to 55 pounds when full grown. Eli is current on his vaccines and his adoption fee will include his future neuter, rabies, and microchip.
